The paper focuses on enabling robots to express their internal states through their motion timing, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The study also involves investigating how users perceive and interpret the robot's motion timing, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The development of mathematical models for user inference from the timing involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the manipulation of objects by the robot and the potential application of the findings to improve robot motion in real-world scenarios may also involve computer vision (cs.CV).
